<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Cluster on PIGSTY</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/</link><description>Recent content in Cluster on PIGSTY</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>PGSQL Cluster</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-cluster/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-cluster/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Main dashboard for a PGSQL cluster: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-cluster"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Cluster is the main dashboard for a single PostgreSQL cluster, providing cluster-level core metrics overview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-cluster"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-cluster.webp" alt="pgsql-cluster"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGRDS Cluster</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgrds-cluster/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgrds-cluster/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RDS version of PGSQL Cluster: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgrds-cluster"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGRDS Cluster is the RDS version of PGSQL Cluster, focusing on PostgreSQL-native metrics without host-level metrics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgrds-cluster"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgrds-cluster.webp" alt="pgrds-cluster"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGSQL Activity</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-activity/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-activity/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Session/load/QPS/TPS/locks for PGSQL cluster: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-activity"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Activity focuses on session activity, load, QPS, TPS, and lock status for a PostgreSQL cluster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-activity"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-activity.webp" alt="pgsql-activity"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGSQL Replication</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-replication/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-replication/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Replication, slots, and pub/sub for PGSQL cluster: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-replication"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Replication focuses on replication status, replication slots, and logical replication (pub/sub) for a PostgreSQL cluster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-replication"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-replication.webp" alt="pgsql-replication"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGSQL Service</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-service/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-service/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Service, proxy, routing, and load balancing for PGSQL cluster: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-service"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Service focuses on service endpoints, proxy routing, and load balancing status for a PostgreSQL cluster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-service"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-service.webp" alt="pgsql-service"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGSQL Databases</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-databases/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-databases/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Database CRUD, slow queries, and table statistics: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-databases"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Databases focuses on database-level CRUD operations, slow queries, and table statistics across all instances in a cluster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-databases"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-databases.webp" alt="pgsql-databases"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGSQL Patroni</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-patroni/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-patroni/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HA status and Patroni component status: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-patroni"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL Patroni focuses on high-availability status and Patroni component health for a PostgreSQL cluster.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-patroni"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-patroni.webp" alt="pgsql-patroni"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>PGSQL PITR</title><link>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-pitr/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pigsty.io/docs/pgsql/dashboard/cluster/pgsql-pitr/</guid><description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PITR context for point-in-time recovery: &lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-pitr"&gt;Demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGSQL PITR provides context information for point-in-time recovery operations, showing backup status and WAL timeline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://demo.pigsty.io/d/pgsql-pitr"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pigsty.io/img/panel/pgsql-pitr.webp" alt="pgsql-pitr"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>